OL,3,CNew mothers 'should do two hours of
OL,4,Cmoderate to vigorous exercise every
OL,5,Cweek'
OL,7,FNew mothers should aim for two hours
OL,8,Fof moderate to vigorous exercise every
OL,9,Fweek, such as brisk walking or
OL,10,Fcycling, researchers say.
OL,12,FGetting back to exercise in the first
OL,13,F12 weeks after birth will help boost
OL,14,Fboth physical and mental health and
OL,15,Fimprove sleep, according to a study.
