OL,3,CNew mothers 'should do two hours of
OL,4,Cmoderate to vigorous exercise every
OL,5,Cweek'
OL,7,FAfter looking at existing research,
OL,8,Fexperts produced a "strong
OL,9,Frecommendation" for new mothers to
OL,10,Fspend at least 120 minutes a week
OL,11,Fdoing such exercise, spread over four
OL,12,For more days of the week.
OL,14,FThis should incorporate a variety of
OL,15,Faerobic and resistance training, they
OL,16,Fsaid.
OL,18,FResistance training includes things
OL,19,Fsuch as using gym machines or doing
OL,20,Fexercises including sit ups, squats,
OL,21,Fpush ups, leg raises and planks.
